Merge #12261

12261: fix(backend/display): prevent nonsensical stack output diff when exporting `Resource` instances r=Frassle a=theneva

# Description

Hi! :wave:

## Background

I use the Node.js SDK to manage a bunch of different Pulumi projects. The entrypoints create some appropriate `Resource` instances, and then export those instances as stack outputs.

That works just fine, except for one thing: Whenever I run a `preview` with one or more unchanged stack output `Resource`s, all `Resource` instances always get printed as if they were changed, with no changed properties:

<img width="713" alt="image" src="https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/1404650/220653823-d4fb2dc3-9afb-4b15-8e75-bd09a235a220.png">

The outputs get printed as if they have diff because the Node.js SDK assigns a property ``@isPulumiResource:` true` to the Resource instance before sending it to the the backend, so that the backend knows to look for internal properties (names starting with `__`).

The backend already attempts to handle the ``@isPulumiResource`` property, but stumbles when the Resource is specifically an unchanged stack output.

It doesn't look too bad in my screenshot, but it gets pretty annoying in bigger stacks. For example, I have a `monitoring` stack that deploys tools like Grafana, Prometheus, Tempo, and Loki, and exposes a bunch of stack outputs to let other stacks know how apps should push their traces, and so on. In practice, the wrongful printing requires me to always scroll up a bunch after running `preview`.

## Patch

I found that removing the `Diff` if it doesn't have any changes left after being "massaged" prevents the wrongful printing, so the fix ends up being pretty neat and contained.

With the patch applied, the output looks like I expected, as there is no diff in the stack outputs:

<img width="605" alt="image" src="https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/1404650/220658047-90e1e996-ad99-4cb5-bba3-14e390074dbf.png">

I don't know if the issue is specific to the Node.js SDK, but seeing as `backend/display` already has code relating to this behaviour, I believe this is a good place for the patch.

## Other stuff

The code for the project I've used to test it is available at https://github.com/theneva/pulumi-stack-output-diff – and `index.ts` in its entirety looks like this:

```ts
import { Resource } from '`@pulumi/pulumi';`

class Taxi extends Resource {
  readonly size = 'big';
  readonly color = 'yellow';

  constructor() {
    super('some:demo:Taxi', 'taxi', false);
  }
}

class Vehicles extends Resource {
  readonly taxi = new Taxi();

  constructor() {
    super('some:demo:Vehicles', 'vehicles', false);
  }
}

export const vehicles = new Vehicles();
```

